This paper deals with the design of protocol sequences for a communication channel with multiple packet reception capability. This involves the study of information theory, network protocols, data structures, signal processing, and multimedia communication. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
